RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 8 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 8 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PINO IN A PURSE led the way up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and held off a late closer to the wire. GIRLS IN CHARGE chased the leader between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole, switched to the outside in upper stretch and gained ground to the wire. DR. ANN raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the turn from the two path, improved position in upper stretch and finished evenly. JLO CAN DANCE trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, and improved position in the lane while never threatening the top two. CHECK THE GRADE tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the bend and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONRADO dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and drew off to the wire. FISHERMAN OSCAR chased the leaders up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the bend, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and kept on to the wire, the best of the rest. MORE DRAMA dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn, gave way entering the stretch and weakened further in the final furlong. ICETECA trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and made no bid. DON CINCO veered out leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and was empty in the lane. MIND FLAYER raced off the pace on the outside early, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 8. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONIQUES DAREDEVIL raced in the two path around the first turn, led the field on the inside racing up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the second bend, kicked clear in the stretch and drew off to the wire. TOOLEGITTOQUIT stalked the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn, and chased the winner home, no match for that rival late. WORKING OVERTIME raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace, began to improve position while racing in the four path around the second turn and finished evenly. ANNIE UP BUCK saved ground around the first turn, chase the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and faded in the lane. GRANDMARY pressed the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, dropped back while racing in the three path around the far bend and continued to tire from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIDINGANDABETTING dueled on the inside up the backstretch, chased the leader from the two path around the turn and pulled clear in the stretch. EL POLICIA dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, led the way while saving ground around the bend, gave way entering the stretch and kept on to the wire. LIL BULL raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and continued to improve position in the lane. HAD RIGHT trailed the field up the backstretch, began to improve position while racing in the three and four path around the turn and continued to gain in the stretch. RUNAWAY TOM raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening stages, navigated the turn from the two path and was empty in the lane. WILD IRISHMAN raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid. PRETTY DUDE chased the leaders between horses early, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the stretch.

CANNON'S ROAR stalked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the two path coming around the second bend and gained ground late. HARROW raced in the two path early, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole and gained ground in the lane. TWO STEPPIN KLUKI saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, continued to save ground around the far turn and gained ground mildly in the stretch. SEVEN CHANNELS saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and flattened out in the lane. CHESS MASTER led the field on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the second bend and tired in the stretch. OBIWAN saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and faded in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WOOTDAREITIS pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and pulled clear. GET EVEN led the field on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to show the way while racing in the two path around the bend, dueled in the lane and gave way in the final sixteenth. CALLE DE BOYD raced off the pace early, navigated the turn from the four path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. WARP SPEED BEAST trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the bend, swung wide entering the stretch and passed tiring horses to the wire. PEINADITO stalked the pace setters on the outside through the opening quarter, challenged from the four path coming around the turn and weakened in the lane. TAKEOVER KASH chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the bend and tired further from there. EL BAILADOR tracked the frontrunners between horses early, raced in the two path around the turn and faded in the stretch.

SUMMER BEE raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the three path and kept on to the wire. LOVE ME NOT bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced off the pace in the three path through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the four path and gained ground late. RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1 1/16M Turf CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Th an $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAZACHAN raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far turn, kicked clear and held that margin to the wire. LIZQUEENFLUERDELIS raced in the four path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the three path, offered a bid nearing the quarter pole and gained ground late. LEGEND'S SONG tracked the leaders from the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn, began a bid entering the stretch, dueled and gave way late. GUIDANCE raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the inside, came around the far bend in the four path, swung wider still entering the stretch and gained ground late to the wire. LIBERTALIA hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace between horses for the run up the backstretch, improved position from the three path coming around the far turn and was outkicked in the stretch. UNKOALAFIED raced in the middle of the pack on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and finished evenly while never threatening. SHES SKY HIGH brushed with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, angled in to save ground around the far bend and weakened in the lane. FREEDOM EXPRESS broke slowly, was rank in the early going, raced into traffic and checked slightly the first time by, navigated the first turn from the four path, floated wide into the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field from the three path around the far turn and was empty in the stretch. TEA'S DREAM brushed with the horse to her inside at the start, angled over to show the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, gave way while racing on the rail around the far turn and tired quickly from there.
